. Procedural democracy is a default position. Its laws and equitable procedures defend people or systems having diverse interests when society fails to create a public that would govern for the common interest.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aInterpersonal relations. 0aReciprocity (Psychology) 0aReciprocity (Psychology). 0aValues. 4aGesellschaftlicher Zusammenhalt. 4aMoralität. 4aMoralkodex. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh  aMoral Codes.  aMorality.  aSocial Cohesion.  aZones.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2014z9783110370393oZDB-23-DPH0 cprintz978311035192740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311035261040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110352610423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110352610/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DPHb2014